se <- function(x) {
    sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))
}

# 95% CI for non normal variables: use bootstrapping
zk <- NULL  
n <- 30
for (i in 1:10000) {
    zk[i] <- mean(sample(d$zombies_killed, n, replace = FALSE))
}
quantile(zk, c(0.025, 0.975))
##     2.5%    97.5% 
## 2.400000 3.633333
